body:
Thanks for the explanation. I see the support in `configuration.py` for reading environment variables. Per the comments, it looks like ENV VARs trump (have precedence) config file values. I'm not a fan of having config in 2 places. More often than not, it results in unexpected behavior.

Why not place config exclusively in the file?

@mistercrunch This feature of having config in 2 places seems like more of a timebomb than a necessary feature. Thoughts?

@criccomini Can you close this? It should be fixed. 

Also, refer to @mistercrunch's question about use-cases for naming dags starting with a digit in the referenced PR #944 

We (Agari) don't have such a use-case.
